    <text id="B0384T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Hoffman states that he will be coming to Staunton to settle accounts with a
                    Richard Banheart, presumably a former employee.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-01-16"><abbr expan="January">Jay</abbr> 16th 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Sangersville</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I received your note of the eleventh in regard to Richard Banheart's work. I will
                    come up next week and settle with him, if no providential <orig
                        reg="interference">interferance</orig> I would have come before now, but his
                    clothes is <orig reg="here">hear</orig>, and I did not want to come <orig
                        reg="until">untill</orig> I could come with the wagon, and bring his
                    clothes.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>J.F. Hoffman</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Thomas">To</abbr> P Jackson</name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
